csum=CashID [[https://gitlab.com/cashid/protocol-specification|#]] is a bad implementation of this because of the "metadata" part.  This means that service providers can request personal information including IP address be linked to your wallet identity.  This will allow blockchain analytics to easily link your government identity to your blockchain money.  The best implementation is just logging in a with a public key and the signature.  You could have a form autofill function from a standard wallet. 
ctime=1631508028
name=NatureVault.PublicKeyAuthentication
rev=4
